The former Executive Chairman of Ijokoro Local Council Development Area (LCDA) Lagos State, Hassan Ajeigbe Amje, has given his total support to Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu, former Lagos State Governor and national leader of ruling party All Progressives Congress (APC), on his ambition to contest 2023 presidency. He said Tinubu is capable of leading Nigeria well, if he is eventually elected President come 2023. A strong member of APC in OjokoroIjaiye Area, Amje said, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu is politically matured enough to give Nigeria a sense of belonging where no man will be oppressed. He knows what it takes to develop and salvage the country. “He also knows where the shoe pinches and how to solve Nigerians’ problems.” He further added that anyone who is against Tinubu’s political ambition for the Presidency is a mere jealous man and this should not deter him over the ongoing campaign. On President Muhammadu Buhari, “He is trying to solve the ills militating against the country but we need to co-operate with him at all levels.